                n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#102)]" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d710a-102">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—At a meeting of the United States and Soviet Chiefs of Staff on July 26,
                        <persName corresp="#p_AAGAI1">Army General Antonov</persName> stated that
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName> had handed to <persName
                        corresp="#p_TJV1">Truman</persName> the Soviet answer to <ref
                        target="#d1279">document No. 1279</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, at 11
                    a.m. on July 25 (see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_408">page
                        408</ref>). No other record of this transaction, which presumably took place
                    at the Cecilienhof Palace immediately before the Ninth Plenary Meeting, has been
                    found.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
